The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 1,050) This two-DVD set captures a 1992 tribute to the remarkable 

Freddie Mercury, who died of AIDS the previous year. Joining the remaining members 

of Queen on stage are artistes like Robert Plant, Paul Young, Lisa Stansfield, 

David Bowie, Elton John and George Michael. And they all perform classic Queen 

covers.

 THE FILM FEST

 (Max Mueller Bhavan and Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, December 

13-16) Featuring a cluster of documentary and short films from Latin America, 

Africa and Asia, the Human Rights Film Festival gets underway with Antonio Zirion?s 

award-winning film Voces de la Guerrero.

THE BOOK

 (Hyatt 

Regency, 7.30 pm, December 18) Actor Shashi Kapoor turns up to promote his book, 

published by Roli, on 25 years of Prithvi Theatre. Film-maker Mrinal Sen will 

be chief guest. 




